		<td><b>PowerPak menu editing</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My cousin has to use his NES and PowerPak with a half-broken TV. Each scanline is offset to the right by a random distance, much like the "fuzz out" in the second dose of <a href="http://www.pineight.com/tod/" class="postlink">Lockjaw: The Overdose</a>. The more black in the image, the more ragged the horizontal sync is. Depending on the amount of black, this could range from a 2-pixel range to an 8-pixel range. And guess how much black is in the PowerPak menu system.
<br />
<br />So would it be feasible to edit the PowerPak menu? He wants to do the following:
<br /><ul><li>Turn on the monochrome bit or otherwise set the background to $00 gray (not $0F black) </li><li>Change the font to make the letters used in Game Genie codes more distinctive </li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


